					<head>Halakhah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85071588" rend="visible">
						<summary>A fragment of a polemic treatise against the Rabbanite code of laws as laid down in Maimonides' Mishneh Torah.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="jrb-Hebr" otherLangs="he">Judeo-Arabic</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85071588">
							<locus from="1r" to="109v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">A Karaite polemical treatise</title>
							<note>
								<p>Contains portions of the fourth and fifth part of the work.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 15th to 16th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="chart">
								<extent>109 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>175</height>
										<width>130</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>140</height>
										<width>100</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>109 folios (+ 2 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). </p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>10 quires of 10 leaves each, marked with Hebrew letters on the upper right-hand corner at the beginning of each quire, and with Arabic numerals on the upper left-hand corners. </p>
									<p>The numeration of quires starts with no. 5, which indicates that the first four quires, together with the first leaf of the fifth quire are missing.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Much damaged. Some leaves restored (stuck on modern paper).</p>
									<p>Worm-eaten.</p>
									<p>Defective at the end.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="13" writtenLines="13">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Visible mastara ruling.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
